This paper presents a novel approach to haptic teleoperation of quadrotor UAVs using control barrier functions (CBFs) to generate force feedback. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to robotics and control systems (cs.RO), as well as systems and control (cs.SY). The use of haptic feedback also falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves mathematical optimization and control theory, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
